   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE IN HIS HUMAN LIVING Scripture Reading: 1 Tim 3:16; Phil 2:7-8; John 3:17; Matt 9:10-13; Luke 4:19-22a; Acts 10:38; Isa 53:2; Luke 2:7, 12, 40, 52, 42, 46-47, 49; 3:23; Isa 53:3; Matt 13:55-57; Luke 4:28-30; Matt 26:4, 16; 4:1, 11 OUTLINE God manifested in the flesh 1 Tim 3:16: Taking the form of a slave, becoming in the likeness of men, found in fashion as a man Phil 2:7-8.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>To express the eternal, infinite, invisible, glorious, omnipotent, omniscient, and omnipresent God through the mortal, finite, visible, inglorious man, limited in power, knowledge, and presence: Divinity unveiled in humanity.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The divine attributes shown in the human virtues.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The divine life mingled with the human life to have one living without a third entity.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In mercy, love, and grace, and not in the condemnation of the law John 3:17: Exhibiting that God desires mercy Matt 9:10-13.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Proclaiming God's acceptable year of jubilee through the words of grace proceeding out of His mouth Luke 4:19-22a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Under the anointing of the Holy Spirit and the divine power with the presence of God Acts 10:38: To declare the Triune God in doing good.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To show people the power of God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To heal the people oppressed by the devil.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>In the stages of human life: Growing before Jehovah as a tender plant and as a root out of dry ground Isa 53:2.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In babyhood Luke 2:7, 12: Wrapped in swaddling clothes.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Lying in a manger.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In boyhood: Growing in wisdom and stature, in the grace of God, and in favor with God and men Luke 2:40, 52.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Caring for the things of God at the age of twelve Luke 2:42, 46-47, 49.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In maturity: To begin His ministry for God at the age of thirty Luke 3:23.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To be a man of sorrows, suffering the despising, rejection, and persecution of man Isa 53:3; Matt 13:55-57; Luke 4:28-30; Matt 26:4, 16.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To be tempted by the devil: Led by the Spirit Matt 4:1.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Defeating the devil and being ministered to by the angels Matt 4:11.</S>
   </TEXT>
